1
00:00:11.428 --> 00:00:12.554  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Sell at 20.

2
00:00:12.637 --> 00:00:14.097  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Is that a joke?

3
00:00:14.180 --> 00:00:16.224  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Do I look like I'm joking?

4
00:00:17.058 --> 00:00:18.268  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Evade.

5
00:00:22.021 --> 00:00:23.356  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
She has him.

6
00:00:23.440 --> 00:00:25.817  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-She's down 50 strips.
-Not for long.

7
00:00:26.317 --> 00:00:28.028  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What makes you so sure?

8
00:00:28.486 --> 00:00:31.239  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, Jadzia's playing a very deep game.

9
00:00:31.322 --> 00:00:34.034  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Her strategy will become
apparent any moment now.

10
00:00:34.117 --> 00:00:35.452  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I see.

11
00:00:36.703 --> 00:00:40.790  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You have absolutely no idea
how this game is played, do you?

12
00:00:42.667 --> 00:00:44.169  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-No.
-( chuckles )

13
00:00:44.252 --> 00:00:46.796  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
But I have developed
a new appreciation for it.

14
00:00:46.880 --> 00:00:49.966  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Oh? Since when?
-Since I married a Tongo player.

15
00:00:50.550 --> 00:00:52.635  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But one thing I am certain about--

16
00:00:52.719 --> 00:00:55.096  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
She will defeat the Ferengi bartender.

17
00:00:55.180 --> 00:00:57.849  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I don't know about that.
Quark's on a roll.

18
00:00:57.932 --> 00:01:01.811  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
In the last month,
he's won 206 straight games.

19
00:01:03.980 --> 00:01:06.357  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Would you care to make
a wager on the outcome?

20
00:01:06.441 --> 00:01:09.194  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Oh, I wouldn't want to bet
against a man's wife.

21
00:01:09.277 --> 00:01:12.155  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Well, if you are afraid--
-Name your stakes.

22
00:01:12.947 --> 00:01:16.451  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
One bottle of bloodwine
against one bottle of scotch whiskey.

23
00:01:16.534 --> 00:01:17.702  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Done.

24
00:01:19.913 --> 00:01:22.499  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
A sale at 50 and a purchase at 100.

25
00:01:25.251 --> 00:01:28.588  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Pretty big talk for
a lady who's lost 50 strips.

26
00:01:28.671 --> 00:01:30.757  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Are you afraid I can't cover my bets?

27
00:01:30.840 --> 00:01:31.966  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Perish the thought!

28
00:01:32.050 --> 00:01:35.094  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I just hate to kick
somebody when they're down.

29
00:01:35.178 --> 00:01:38.848  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll buy at 100... and confront.

30
00:01:39.766 --> 00:01:42.894  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, if you're gonna kick me,
I'm gonna have to kick back.

31
00:01:42.977 --> 00:01:44.312  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
QUARK: unbelievable.

32
00:01:44.521 --> 00:01:45.980  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( exclaims in native langauge )

33
00:01:47.607 --> 00:01:50.401  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I like my bloodwine
very young and very sweet.

34
00:01:51.528 --> 00:01:54.030  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Is he a friend of yours?
-Just a fan.

35
00:01:54.572 --> 00:01:57.575  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm afraid I'm going to have
to disappoint all your fans.

36
00:02:00.245 --> 00:02:01.579  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
A full consortium?

37
00:02:01.663 --> 00:02:03.581  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
207.

38
00:02:03.665 --> 00:02:06.876  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
A single malt,
preferably something from the highlands.

39
00:02:07.460 --> 00:02:08.962  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I will need some time.

40
00:02:09.045 --> 00:02:10.463  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, your credit's good.

41
00:02:14.050 --> 00:02:16.636  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Whoo, 207 straight.

42
00:02:16.719 --> 00:02:19.556  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
QUARK: 36 strips of gold press latinum.

43
00:02:22.267 --> 00:02:24.519  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Did you lose a bet?
-It is of no consequence.

44
00:02:24.602 --> 00:02:26.521  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm sorry about that.

45
00:02:29.691 --> 00:02:33.611  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I would rather lose a bet on you
than win on someone else.

46
00:02:33.695 --> 00:02:36.072  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Ooh, good response.

47
00:02:44.122 --> 00:02:46.332  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Are you still running
that drill tomorrow afternoon?

48
00:02:46.416 --> 00:02:48.001  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I was planning to. Why?

49
00:02:48.084 --> 00:02:50.670  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Because I wanted to recalibrate
the external sensors

50
00:02:50.753 --> 00:02:53.673  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
before the night watch comes on duty.

51
00:02:54.173 --> 00:02:56.718  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We should be done by 1600 hours.

52
00:02:56.801 --> 00:02:58.595  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, I think that'll work.

53
00:02:59.929 --> 00:03:04.392  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Oh, the <i>Sutherland </i>is going to
be here the day after tomorrow and...

54
00:03:20.992 --> 00:03:23.286  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-You were saying?
-Nothing.

55
00:03:28.875 --> 00:03:30.793  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I don't feel like talking anymore.

56
00:03:51.648 --> 00:03:53.274  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-( beep )
<i>-Kira to Worf.</i>

57
00:04:02.158 --> 00:04:03.451  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Worf here.

58
00:04:03.534 --> 00:04:06.204  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
KIRA:<i> Sorry to bother you, Commander,</i>
<i>but I need to see you and Jadzia</i>

59
00:04:06.287 --> 00:04:08.373  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>in the Captain's office, immediately.</i>

60
00:04:08.456 --> 00:04:09.999  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We're on our way.

61
00:04:18.007 --> 00:04:20.134  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Jadzia... Get up.

62
00:04:20.218 --> 00:04:21.594  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm coming!

63
00:04:22.303 --> 00:04:23.763  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hey!

64
00:04:24.180 --> 00:04:26.724  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We don't have a lot of time,
so I'll get right to it.

65
00:04:26.808 --> 00:04:28.351  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
For the last two months,

66
00:04:28.434 --> 00:04:31.104  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Starfleet has been receiving
military intelligence

67
00:04:31.187 --> 00:04:32.772  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
from a Cardassian operative.

68
00:04:32.855 --> 00:04:35.149  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
That operative has now sent
an emergency signal

69
00:04:35.233 --> 00:04:39.153  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
indicating he needs to speak to someone
in a face-to-face conversation.

70
00:04:39.237 --> 00:04:40.488  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
In 13 hours,

71
00:04:40.571 --> 00:04:42.907  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
he'll beam an encrypted
subspace transmission

72
00:04:42.991 --> 00:04:45.243  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
to these coordinates in the badlands.

73
00:04:45.326 --> 00:04:46.953  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Who is the operative?

74
00:04:47.036 --> 00:04:49.747  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Intelligence told me that
his name is Lasaran,

75
00:04:49.831 --> 00:04:51.791  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But that's all they'll say about him.

76
00:04:51.874 --> 00:04:55.670  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
They did emphasize several times that
he is very important to them

77
00:04:55.753 --> 00:04:58.715  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and that we should send someone
to the badlands as soon as possible.

78
00:04:59.382 --> 00:05:01.551  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So, with the <i>Defiant </i>gone,

79
00:05:01.634 --> 00:05:05.138  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and most of the runabouts off on exercises
with the Ninth Fleet...

80
00:05:05.221 --> 00:05:07.307  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We just volunteered for
a trip to the badlands.

81
00:05:07.390 --> 00:05:08.516  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Afraid so.

82
00:05:08.599 --> 00:05:11.394  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The <i>Shenandoah's </i>prepped
and ready to go on landing pad "A."

83
00:05:11.477 --> 00:05:12.478  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Good luck.

84
00:07:29.907 --> 00:07:31.409  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
-No.
-No?

85
00:07:31.492 --> 00:07:33.202  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
No, I'm not going to spend two weeks

86
00:07:33.286 --> 00:07:36.038  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
hiking across Vulcan's forge
in the middle of their summer.

87
00:07:36.122 --> 00:07:38.207  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
I thought you always
wanted to see the forge.

88
00:07:38.291 --> 00:07:41.419  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
See it, yes. Honeymoon there, no.

89
00:07:41.502 --> 00:07:43.421  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Well, there's a mountain-climbing
expedition on Andor

90
00:07:43.504 --> 00:07:44.505  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
that caught my attention.

91
00:07:44.589 --> 00:07:47.383  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Worf... My love...

92
00:07:47.467 --> 00:07:49.051  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Let me make this very clear.

93
00:07:49.135 --> 00:07:51.345  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
I do not want to spend my honeymoon

94
00:07:51.429 --> 00:07:55.475  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
climbing, hiking, sweating, bleeding,
or suffering in any way.

95
00:07:56.392 --> 00:07:58.561  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
-All right, what do you want?
-Room service.

96
00:07:58.644 --> 00:07:59.687  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
-Room service?
-Room service.

97
00:07:59.770 --> 00:08:00.897  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
I want to be pampered.

98
00:08:00.980 --> 00:08:03.274  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
I want a staff to cater to our every whim.

99
00:08:03.357 --> 00:08:06.319  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
I want to be embarrassed
by the size of our room.

100
00:08:06.402 --> 00:08:09.030  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
I want a balcony with a view
that would make you want

101
00:08:09.113 --> 00:08:11.824  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
to break down and cry
from the sheer beauty of it all.

102
00:08:11.908 --> 00:08:15.369  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
And I don't want to spend
one moment of our honeymoon

103
00:08:15.453 --> 00:08:16.871  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
suffering from anything

104
00:08:16.954 --> 00:08:20.500  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
except guilt about
our complete self-indulgence.

105
00:08:21.250 --> 00:08:22.251  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Risa.

106
00:08:22.335 --> 00:08:23.544  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Not this time.

107
00:08:24.921 --> 00:08:26.964  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Welcome to Casperia Prime,

108
00:08:27.048 --> 00:08:29.926  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
the vacation capital
of the Horvarian cluster.

109
00:08:33.596 --> 00:08:35.598  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You have been planning this all along.

110
00:08:36.098 --> 00:08:38.809  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, it seemed fair.
You did plan the wedding.

111
00:08:40.311 --> 00:08:41.854  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Very well. Room service.

112
00:08:41.938 --> 00:08:44.148  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Really?
-Really.

113
00:08:44.232 --> 00:08:45.483  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, that was easy.

114
00:08:46.400 --> 00:08:47.985  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Did you want to fight over it?

115
00:08:48.069 --> 00:08:49.654  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No. It's just...

116
00:08:49.737 --> 00:08:52.365  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I didn't expect you
to surrender so quickly.

117
00:08:52.448 --> 00:08:54.033  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Surrender?
-Bad word.

118
00:08:54.116 --> 00:08:55.868  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Very bad.
-OK.

119
00:08:55.952 --> 00:09:00.081  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
But you have to admit you've been
unusually...accommodating lately.

120
00:09:00.957 --> 00:09:02.250  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What is wrong with that?

121
00:09:02.333 --> 00:09:04.335  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Nothing. It's just...

122
00:09:04.418 --> 00:09:05.670  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Unusual.

123
00:09:05.753 --> 00:09:06.963  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Are you feeling all right?

124
00:09:07.046 --> 00:09:08.756  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I am a married man.

125
00:09:09.423 --> 00:09:13.135  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I have to make certain...
adjustments in my lifestyle.

126
00:09:13.219 --> 00:09:15.054  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Adjustments?

127
00:09:15.137 --> 00:09:17.265  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Worf, you're practically easygoing.

128
00:09:17.348 --> 00:09:18.766  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What's next, a sense of humor?

129
00:09:18.849 --> 00:09:20.851  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I have a sense of humor.

130
00:09:21.561 --> 00:09:24.272  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
On the <i>Enterprise,</i>
I was considered to be quite amusing.

131
00:09:24.689 --> 00:09:26.649  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, that must've been one dull ship.

132
00:09:28.150 --> 00:09:29.443  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That is a joke!

133
00:09:29.527 --> 00:09:30.695  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I get it.

134
00:09:30.778 --> 00:09:32.780  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It is not funny, but I get it.

135
00:09:32.863 --> 00:09:35.575  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I don't know if I can
get used to the new you.

136
00:09:35.658 --> 00:09:37.076  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's kind of eerie.

137
00:09:37.159 --> 00:09:40.288  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Your problem is
you cannot accept change.

138
00:09:40.371 --> 00:09:43.124  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-I can't accept change?
-That is correct.

139
00:09:43.207 --> 00:09:44.750  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, you've got to be kidding.

140
00:09:44.834 --> 00:09:47.044  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I've changed bodies six times, Worf.

141
00:09:47.128 --> 00:09:49.589  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Yes, but you are still
very set in your ways.

142
00:09:50.089 --> 00:09:52.008  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And look who's talking.

143
00:09:52.091 --> 00:09:55.928  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, I do not have to sleep
on the same side of the bed every night,

144
00:09:56.012 --> 00:09:59.265  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
or brush my hair exactly 50 strokes
every night,

145
00:09:59.348 --> 00:10:01.851  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
or eat the same thing
for breakfast every day,

146
00:10:01.934 --> 00:10:04.520  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
or read the last page of the book
before the beginning,

147
00:10:04.604 --> 00:10:06.647  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-or lift up--
-I get the point.

148
00:10:07.315 --> 00:10:10.568  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I don't know how you can live
with someone so monotonous.

149
00:10:11.402 --> 00:10:12.695  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It is not easy.

150
00:10:15.364 --> 00:10:16.949  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That was a joke.

151
00:10:18.701 --> 00:10:22.997  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
This is going to be
a very, very long trip.

152
00:10:31.088 --> 00:10:32.506  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( door chimes )

153
00:10:32.590 --> 00:10:33.883  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Come in.

154
00:10:34.967 --> 00:10:36.552  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You're not dressed.

155
00:10:37.053 --> 00:10:39.347  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Is it time?
-1700 on the dot.

156
00:10:39.430 --> 00:10:40.848  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We have the holosuite
for the next three hours,

157
00:10:40.931 --> 00:10:41.932  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and we're going to
need every minute of it.

158
00:10:42.016 --> 00:10:44.352  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Three British agents have disappeared
in West Berlin.

159
00:10:44.435 --> 00:10:47.897  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Now, M.I. Five suspect
the Soviets were involved of course.

160
00:10:47.980 --> 00:10:50.358  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
However, the Americans
have intercepted a, uh...

161
00:10:50.441 --> 00:10:52.276  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What are you doing with a Tongo wheel?

162
00:10:52.360 --> 00:10:54.195  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm brushing up on my game.

163
00:10:54.278 --> 00:10:56.238  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-You play Tongo?
-Sure.

164
00:10:57.239 --> 00:10:59.033  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, I used to.

165
00:11:00.368 --> 00:11:02.912  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
That is, I played the game once,
a long time ago,

166
00:11:02.995 --> 00:11:06.957  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
with a Ferengi privateer
and a Romulan mercenary.

167
00:11:07.041 --> 00:11:08.125  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Fascinating.

168
00:11:08.209 --> 00:11:11.962  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Anyway, the Americans have intercepted
a series of messages from Istanbul

169
00:11:12.046 --> 00:11:13.756  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
to a remote island in the South Pacific

170
00:11:13.839 --> 00:11:14.965  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-which might indicate--
-Let's play a hand.

171
00:11:15.049 --> 00:11:16.050  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Miles...

172
00:11:16.133 --> 00:11:17.551  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Just one hand.
-Why?

173
00:11:17.635 --> 00:11:18.803  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I need the practice.

174
00:11:18.886 --> 00:11:20.304  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sighs )

175
00:11:20.388 --> 00:11:22.348  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I want to beat Quark.

176
00:11:22.431 --> 00:11:23.557  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Good luck.

177
00:11:23.641 --> 00:11:25.476  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Luck has nothing to do with it.

178
00:11:25.559 --> 00:11:28.896  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Tongo is a game of strategy
and calculated risk.

179
00:11:28.979 --> 00:11:30.022  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I don't even know the rules.

180
00:11:30.106 --> 00:11:31.732  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, here.

181
00:11:31.816 --> 00:11:33.692  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
All right, let's play. I'll deal.

182
00:11:35.027 --> 00:11:38.823  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
WORF: <i>Shenandoah log: Stardate 51597.2.</i>

183
00:11:38.906 --> 00:11:40.950  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>We have arrived </i>
<i>at the designated coordinates</i>

184
00:11:41.033 --> 00:11:44.370  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>near the badlands and are</i>
<i>awaiting the transmission from Lasaran.</i>

185
00:11:46.789 --> 00:11:48.082  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
JADZIA: This is it.

186
00:11:48.165 --> 00:11:50.167  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
A very sophisticated encryption matrix.

187
00:11:50.626 --> 00:11:52.336  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Whoever he is, he's good.

188
00:11:55.339 --> 00:11:56.298  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Who are you?</i>

189
00:11:56.382 --> 00:11:59.427  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm Commander Worf. This is Commander Dax.

190
00:11:59.510 --> 00:12:02.596  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Starfleet Intelligence has sent us here
to receive your transmission.

191
00:12:02.847 --> 00:12:03.931  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>A Klingon.</i>

192
00:12:04.849 --> 00:12:07.017  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Why did they have to send a Klingon?</i>

193
00:12:07.101 --> 00:12:09.562  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm a Trill.
Does that make you feel any better?

194
00:12:09.645 --> 00:12:13.566  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>-Are you trying to be funny?</i>
-Oh, not at all. He's the funny one.

195
00:12:13.649 --> 00:12:16.402  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-What is it you want?
<i>-We'll get to that in a minute.</i>

196
00:12:16.485 --> 00:12:19.321  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>First, I have something </i>
<i>that you want, badly...</i>

197
00:12:19.405 --> 00:12:21.073  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Information on the Founders.</i>

198
00:12:21.365 --> 00:12:23.993  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>I know how many of them</i>
<i>there are in the Alpha Quadrant,</i>

199
00:12:24.076 --> 00:12:26.245  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>where they are, and what they're doing.</i>

200
00:12:26.328 --> 00:12:28.914  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-We're listening.
<i>-I'm sure you are.</i>

201
00:12:28.998 --> 00:12:30.583  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Now let's talk about what I want.</i>

202
00:12:30.666 --> 00:12:32.376  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>I want out, now.</i>

203
00:12:32.460 --> 00:12:33.836  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You want to defect.

204
00:12:33.919 --> 00:12:36.172  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>The Vorta advisor here </i>
<i>is getting suspicious...</i>

205
00:12:36.255 --> 00:12:37.506  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Asking questions,</i>

206
00:12:37.590 --> 00:12:40.092  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>making a lot of routine </i>
<i>security checks in my section.</i>

207
00:12:40.176 --> 00:12:42.052  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>I can't stay here any longer.</i>

208
00:12:42.136 --> 00:12:43.179  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
WORF: Very well.

209
00:12:43.262 --> 00:12:45.514  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We will relay your message
to Starfleet Intelligence

210
00:12:45.598 --> 00:12:47.141  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and they will arrange to bring you out.

211
00:12:47.224 --> 00:12:49.143  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>I can't wait for them </i>
<i>to make arrangements.</i>

212
00:12:49.226 --> 00:12:53.397  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>In 15 minutes, I am leaving here</i>
<i>for the Dominion base on Soukara,</i>

213
00:12:53.481 --> 00:12:55.483  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>and I have a feeling </i>
<i>this is going to be the last time</i>

214
00:12:55.566 --> 00:12:57.526  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>that they let me leave Cardassia Prime.</i>

215
00:12:57.610 --> 00:13:01.197  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>So, I need to take advantage </i>
<i>of this opportunity.</i>

216
00:13:01.280 --> 00:13:03.782  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Soukara is inside
Dominion-controlled space.

217
00:13:03.866 --> 00:13:07.620  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It will not be easy to make a rendezvous
near that planet without being detected.

218
00:13:07.703 --> 00:13:09.872  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Don't work your brain too hard, Klingon.</i>

219
00:13:09.955 --> 00:13:11.582  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>I've taken care of everything.</i>

220
00:13:11.665 --> 00:13:15.711  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Three days from now </i>
<i>at exactly 1730 hours local time,</i>

221
00:13:15.794 --> 00:13:18.547  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>I will leave the base </i>
<i>and walk into the jungle.</i>

222
00:13:18.631 --> 00:13:21.884  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>It'll be at least two days</i>
<i>before they know I'm missing.</i>

223
00:13:21.967 --> 00:13:25.221  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>All you have to do </i>
<i>is get me off the planet.</i>

224
00:13:25.304 --> 00:13:28.724  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Now, there are transporter scramblers </i>
<i>protecting Soukara</i>

225
00:13:28.807 --> 00:13:30.559  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>so you can't beam me aboard your ship.</i>

226
00:13:30.643 --> 00:13:34.647  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>You're going to have to land</i>
<i>and meet me at a rendezvous point on foot.</i>

227
00:13:35.314 --> 00:13:37.775  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>I am sending you all </i>
<i>the information you'll need</i>

228
00:13:37.858 --> 00:13:40.778  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>to avoid the Dominion sensors </i>
<i>on the ground.</i>

229
00:13:41.237 --> 00:13:42.738  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Follow my instructions.</i>

230
00:13:42.821 --> 00:13:46.784  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Meet me at this rendezvous point</i>
<i>and have a ship waiting.</i>

231
00:13:48.202 --> 00:13:50.871  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We've got the information.
It looks pretty thorough.

232
00:13:50.955 --> 00:13:52.957  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We will need time to study these plans.

233
00:13:53.040 --> 00:13:55.292  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>You haven't been listening. </i>
<i>I don't have time.</i>

234
00:13:55.376 --> 00:13:57.920  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Once I leave here, </i>
<i>I can't contact you again.</i>

235
00:13:58.003 --> 00:14:00.339  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>I have to know if you're</i>
<i>going to be there or not,</i>

236
00:14:00.422 --> 00:14:02.091  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>and I have to know now!</i>

237
00:14:04.843 --> 00:14:06.095  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We will be there.

238
00:14:07.471 --> 00:14:09.265  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>How far I've fallen... </i>( sighs )

239
00:14:10.057 --> 00:14:12.601  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Risking my life on the word of a Klingon.</i>

240
00:14:13.686 --> 00:14:16.188  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Three days. Don't be late.</i>

241
00:14:31.287 --> 00:14:35.082  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
All right.
I'll buy at 30 with sales at 35.

242
00:14:35.165 --> 00:14:38.711  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Buy at 35, sell at 150
and index the margin at 10%.

243
00:14:39.211 --> 00:14:41.714  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Index the margin?
-Miles, give it up.

244
00:14:41.797 --> 00:14:44.300  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-This just isn't your game.
-We'll see about that.

245
00:14:44.383 --> 00:14:45.426  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sighs )

246
00:14:46.343 --> 00:14:47.595  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Evade.

247
00:14:49.388 --> 00:14:50.681  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Do you realize

248
00:14:50.764 --> 00:14:54.184  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
that Quark has won
207 straight games of Tongo?

249
00:14:54.268 --> 00:14:55.394  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So?

250
00:14:55.477 --> 00:14:56.729  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So, someone has to beat him.

251
00:14:56.812 --> 00:14:58.522  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And that someone is you?

252
00:14:58.606 --> 00:14:59.899  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Why not?

253
00:14:59.982 --> 00:15:02.776  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, for one thing, you can't play Tongo.

254
00:15:02.860 --> 00:15:04.236  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Confront.

255
00:15:05.070 --> 00:15:06.530  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( groans ) Damn!

256
00:15:06.614 --> 00:15:09.366  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Had enough?
-Not by a long shot.

257
00:15:09.450 --> 00:15:12.077  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Miles, at this rate,
it's going to take you another 20 years

258
00:15:12.161 --> 00:15:13.579  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
to be ready to take on Quark.

259
00:15:13.662 --> 00:15:14.747  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
One more.

260
00:15:14.830 --> 00:15:16.999  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
( sighs ) Why are you
so determined to beat him?

261
00:15:17.750 --> 00:15:19.376  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-It's the challenge.
-A challenge?

262
00:15:19.877 --> 00:15:21.211  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Isn't it enough?

263
00:15:21.295 --> 00:15:23.047  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I mean, why do you think
I became an engineer, eh?

264
00:15:23.130 --> 00:15:24.757  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The challenge.

265
00:15:24.840 --> 00:15:27.551  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
What do you think's kept me
kayaking down the same river

266
00:15:27.635 --> 00:15:30.137  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
week after week for the last seven years?

267
00:15:30.220 --> 00:15:31.972  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The challenge.

268
00:15:32.056 --> 00:15:34.266  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Why would I keep playing darts
against somebody

269
00:15:34.350 --> 00:15:37.895  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
with a genetically engineered
hand/eye coordination, huh?

270
00:15:37.978 --> 00:15:40.230  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-The challenge.
-Exactly.

271
00:15:42.733 --> 00:15:44.693  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I have to do something
to keep my mind off the fact

272
00:15:44.777 --> 00:15:47.613  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
that Keiko's been away
for the last six months.

273
00:15:49.490 --> 00:15:50.699  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hold on.

274
00:15:51.825 --> 00:15:54.161  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Maybe I can't beat Quark...

275
00:15:54.954 --> 00:15:56.413  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But you can.

276
00:15:57.247 --> 00:15:59.708  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You and that genetically
engineered brain of yours.

277
00:15:59.792 --> 00:16:01.877  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Me? I've only just learned
how to play the game.

278
00:16:01.961 --> 00:16:04.380  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yeah, in about 10 seconds flat!

279
00:16:05.339 --> 00:16:06.799  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We can do it, Julian.

280
00:16:06.882 --> 00:16:08.342  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We can beat him.

281
00:16:08.425 --> 00:16:09.635  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
"We"?

282
00:16:10.469 --> 00:16:11.929  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You're talking about me.

283
00:16:12.012 --> 00:16:15.224  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Yeah, well, you're good at calculation
but a little weak on strategy.

284
00:16:15.641 --> 00:16:18.018  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-I'll be your coach.
-No, thank you.

285
00:16:18.102 --> 00:16:19.853  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Think of it as a challenge.

286
00:16:19.937 --> 00:16:21.730  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's your obsession, Miles, not mine.

287
00:16:21.814 --> 00:16:23.023  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Do it for the latinum.

288
00:16:23.107 --> 00:16:24.316  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Nice try.

289
00:16:24.400 --> 00:16:28.153  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Do it for the satisfaction
of the look on Quark's face

290
00:16:28.237 --> 00:16:32.533  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
when he's beaten at a game of Tongo
by a lowly "hu-man."

291
00:16:33.200 --> 00:16:34.284  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Deal the cards.

292
00:16:43.961 --> 00:16:45.921  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We are approaching the Soukara system.

293
00:16:46.005 --> 00:16:47.423  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Stand by to bring us out of warp.

294
00:16:47.506 --> 00:16:48.674  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Now.

295
00:16:50.342 --> 00:16:52.094  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
There is an asteroid field directly ahead.

296
00:16:52.177 --> 00:16:53.220  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's what we want.

297
00:16:53.303 --> 00:16:55.723  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The Dominion's sensor grid
in the system has three gaps

298
00:16:55.806 --> 00:16:57.850  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and they're all in that asteroid field.

299
00:17:03.188 --> 00:17:04.481  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
JADZIA: Want me to slow down?

300
00:17:04.565 --> 00:17:06.817  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No, unless you think you should.

301
00:17:06.900 --> 00:17:08.861  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Not at all. In fact, we could go faster.

302
00:17:08.944 --> 00:17:10.404  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
By all means.

303
00:17:10.946 --> 00:17:12.990  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Ooh! A man after my own heart.

304
00:17:27.546 --> 00:17:29.298  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Most impressive.

305
00:17:29.381 --> 00:17:32.217  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Nothing that any
300-year-old pilot couldn't do.

306
00:17:32.801 --> 00:17:34.845  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We are being scanned from the surface.

307
00:17:35.137 --> 00:17:37.347  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
JADZIA: Taking evasive maneuvers.

308
00:17:37.431 --> 00:17:38.640  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Did they get a fix on us?

309
00:17:38.724 --> 00:17:40.184  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
WORF: I do not think so.

310
00:17:40.267 --> 00:17:43.103  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
JADZIA: Good. We've come too long a way
just to get shot down.

311
00:17:43.187 --> 00:17:46.148  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If you take the helm,
I'll scan the surface for a landing site.

312
00:17:47.900 --> 00:17:49.860  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
There's the base...

313
00:17:49.943 --> 00:17:51.403  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The rendezvous point...

314
00:17:52.321 --> 00:17:55.074  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And the Dominion sensor perimeter.

315
00:17:55.157 --> 00:17:58.702  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
There's a valley about 20 kilometers
north of the rendezvous point.

316
00:17:59.495 --> 00:18:00.829  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It's a long way to go
on foot in the jungle,

317
00:18:00.913 --> 00:18:04.041  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but I don't think we can risk taking
the ship any closer to their sensors.

318
00:18:04.124 --> 00:18:05.250  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Agreed.

319
00:18:15.260 --> 00:18:17.846  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We have less than two days
to reach the rendezvous point.

320
00:18:17.930 --> 00:18:20.599  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
About 10 kilometers a day,
that shouldn't be too bad.

321
00:18:20.682 --> 00:18:22.768  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Do not underestimate the task ahead.

322
00:18:22.851 --> 00:18:25.854  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We still have to penetrate the sensor grid
and avoid the Dominion patrols.

323
00:18:25.938 --> 00:18:27.439  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sighs ) I know,

324
00:18:27.523 --> 00:18:29.900  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
find a man in the middle
of an alien jungle,

325
00:18:29.983 --> 00:18:31.318  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
then walk him out without getting caught.

326
00:18:31.401 --> 00:18:32.736  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Piece of cake.

327
00:18:32.820 --> 00:18:35.155  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Ready?
-After you.

328
00:18:49.837 --> 00:18:51.213  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
OK.

329
00:18:51.296 --> 00:18:52.714  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Go to 25 joules.

330
00:19:00.889 --> 00:19:02.099  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
WORF: 25 joules.

331
00:19:05.227 --> 00:19:06.311  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Done.

332
00:19:06.395 --> 00:19:07.855  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's it. We're linked.

333
00:19:10.983 --> 00:19:12.067  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Here, check my work.

334
00:19:14.194 --> 00:19:16.572  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Dominion encryption lockouts bypassed,

335
00:19:16.655 --> 00:19:18.824  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
tricorder link to their sensor grids,

336
00:19:18.907 --> 00:19:20.576  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
life signs masked.

337
00:19:20.659 --> 00:19:21.702  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Nicely done.

338
00:19:21.785 --> 00:19:23.203  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Thank you.

339
00:19:26.707 --> 00:19:30.335  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Of course, our tricorders
will be useless from now on.

340
00:19:30.419 --> 00:19:31.587  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
There you go again,

341
00:19:31.670 --> 00:19:33.672  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
looking for the cloud
in the silver lining.

342
00:19:33.755 --> 00:19:36.175  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I am not complaining.

343
00:19:36.258 --> 00:19:37.885  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I look forward to walking
through the jungle

344
00:19:37.968 --> 00:19:41.138  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
without a map
and no idea of what lies ahead.

345
00:19:41.763 --> 00:19:44.433  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, the funny thing is you probably are.

346
00:19:50.522 --> 00:19:52.983  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
This is a Ferengi-only game, gentlemen.

347
00:19:53.066 --> 00:19:54.610  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You let Dax play.

348
00:19:54.693 --> 00:19:57.446  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
She's an exception, the only exception.

349
00:19:57.738 --> 00:19:59.114  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You're afraid I'll clean you out.

350
00:19:59.198 --> 00:20:02.701  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm afraid you'll embarrass yourself
and ruin the game for the rest of us.

351
00:20:02.784 --> 00:20:04.786  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I think I can keep up.

352
00:20:04.870 --> 00:20:07.206  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The question is, can you keep up with me?

353
00:20:07.289 --> 00:20:09.499  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Don't try and scare me
with that genetically engineered

354
00:20:09.583 --> 00:20:11.793  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
intellect of yours, Doctor.

355
00:20:11.877 --> 00:20:14.338  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Tongo is more than just number crunching.

356
00:20:14.421 --> 00:20:17.216  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
They have yet to create the computer
that can master this game.

357
00:20:17.299 --> 00:20:19.551  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Then you shouldn't have
anything to worry about.

358
00:20:20.093 --> 00:20:24.014  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You realize we are not playing for drinks.

359
00:20:24.097 --> 00:20:26.642  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
This is a high stakes game.

360
00:20:27.351 --> 00:20:29.269  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We came to play.

361
00:20:30.520 --> 00:20:31.855  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Gentlemen?

362
00:20:32.439 --> 00:20:33.815  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( grunting )

363
00:20:35.317 --> 00:20:36.693  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
All right.

364
00:20:36.777 --> 00:20:40.155  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The buy-in is five strips,
and you're dealing.

365
00:20:43.784 --> 00:20:46.662  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You better get off to a fast start.

366
00:20:46.745 --> 00:20:48.789  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
They won't know what hit them.

367
00:20:54.253 --> 00:20:56.755  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Buy at 300, sell at 350.

368
00:21:00.217 --> 00:21:03.178  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You're a quick study, Doctor.
I'll give you that.

369
00:21:03.262 --> 00:21:05.430  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You mean quick for a "hu-man,"
don't you, Quark?

370
00:21:05.514 --> 00:21:08.433  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I would never say anything
so distasteful during a game.

371
00:21:08.517 --> 00:21:10.227  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No, you'd wait until it was over.

372
00:21:10.727 --> 00:21:12.312  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Of course.

373
00:21:12.396 --> 00:21:13.605  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Evade.

374
00:21:16.358 --> 00:21:18.151  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Dax was a quick study too.

375
00:21:18.235 --> 00:21:20.362  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
She told me it only took her two weeks
to win her first match.

376
00:21:20.445 --> 00:21:21.738  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's practically unheard of.

377
00:21:21.822 --> 00:21:24.074  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Dax specializes in the unexpected.

378
00:21:24.157 --> 00:21:26.660  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Still buying at 300, selling at four.

379
00:21:27.995 --> 00:21:30.664  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'd like to index the margin at 20%.

380
00:21:30.747 --> 00:21:32.666  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Interesting.

381
00:21:32.749 --> 00:21:35.836  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
She certainly did the unexpected
when she married Commander Boring.

382
00:21:35.919 --> 00:21:37.337  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's for sure.

383
00:21:37.421 --> 00:21:39.673  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
When they first started seeing each other,
I thought,

384
00:21:39.756 --> 00:21:42.759  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
"This can't last. I give it two months."

385
00:21:43.927 --> 00:21:46.263  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll buy at 400...

386
00:21:46.346 --> 00:21:47.556  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And sell at five.

387
00:21:48.307 --> 00:21:49.683  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I had the same thought.

388
00:21:49.766 --> 00:21:51.685  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Although, to tell you the truth,
I only gave it a month.

389
00:21:51.768 --> 00:21:53.228  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Confront.

390
00:21:53.312 --> 00:21:55.397  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
She's a real heart-breaker, that one.

391
00:21:56.940 --> 00:21:58.692  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That she is.

392
00:21:58.775 --> 00:22:02.821  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Leverage the buy-in and sell at 550.

393
00:22:04.281 --> 00:22:06.116  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You know...

394
00:22:06.199 --> 00:22:09.661  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You go through a lot of ups and downs
in my business.

395
00:22:10.454 --> 00:22:14.041  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
There are days when the profits are down,
and the customers are scarce,

396
00:22:14.124 --> 00:22:17.836  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and you think you'll never see
another strip of latinum again,

397
00:22:19.171 --> 00:22:22.341  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And then, Jadzia comes in...

398
00:22:22.424 --> 00:22:25.260  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And flashes that smile of hers.

399
00:22:25.886 --> 00:22:28.972  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Suddenly things
don't seem so bad after all.

400
00:22:29.056 --> 00:22:30.974  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I know exactly what you mean.

401
00:22:31.558 --> 00:22:34.978  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You know,
sometimes she walks past the infirmary,

402
00:22:35.062 --> 00:22:38.190  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and all she has to do is wink,
and somehow, that...

403
00:22:38.273 --> 00:22:40.108  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
makes my whole day look a little brighter.

404
00:22:40.192 --> 00:22:41.860  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Focus, Julian. Focus.

405
00:22:42.486 --> 00:22:43.361  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Shh!

406
00:22:44.488 --> 00:22:48.950  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll, uh, buy that 550, and...

407
00:22:49.868 --> 00:22:51.244  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Index the exchange at 10.

408
00:22:52.079 --> 00:22:53.830  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And now she's married.

409
00:22:53.914 --> 00:22:54.790  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Married.

410
00:22:55.207 --> 00:22:56.374  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Out of reach.

411
00:22:58.210 --> 00:22:59.753  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm converting my reserves...

412
00:23:00.587 --> 00:23:02.255  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And selling at 600.

413
00:23:03.924 --> 00:23:05.759  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You know what's really sad?

414
00:23:05.842 --> 00:23:08.470  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What really keeps me awake at night?

415
00:23:08.553 --> 00:23:11.181  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
She's out of reach because we let her go.

416
00:23:13.391 --> 00:23:15.560  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yes, I suppose so...

417
00:23:15.644 --> 00:23:17.646  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But some things just weren't meant to be.

418
00:23:19.689 --> 00:23:20.690  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Evade.

419
00:23:20.774 --> 00:23:22.067  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Julian!

420
00:23:22.150 --> 00:23:23.527  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Are you sure you want to--

421
00:23:23.610 --> 00:23:26.780  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Chief! Please. You know the rules.

422
00:23:26.863 --> 00:23:28.448  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No coaching during a round.

423
00:23:33.286 --> 00:23:34.830  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You're probably right.

424
00:23:37.374 --> 00:23:39.876  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
But what if that's
a convenient rationalization?

425
00:23:40.961 --> 00:23:45.632  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
What if deep down in our heart of hearts,
we both know she's something unique...

426
00:23:45.715 --> 00:23:47.884  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Something we may never see again,

427
00:23:47.968 --> 00:23:49.719  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
a chance at true happiness?

428
00:23:49.803 --> 00:23:52.514  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And we let her slip through our fingers.

429
00:23:52.973 --> 00:23:55.142  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
What if 50 years from now
we each look back

430
00:23:55.225 --> 00:23:58.019  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and say, "What a fool I was"?

431
00:24:02.607 --> 00:24:03.859  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Confront.

432
00:24:04.734 --> 00:24:05.861  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Doctor?

433
00:24:05.944 --> 00:24:07.195  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hmm?

434
00:24:07.279 --> 00:24:08.613  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Confront.

435
00:24:08.697 --> 00:24:10.073  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh.

436
00:24:10.157 --> 00:24:11.616  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Sorry. Um...

437
00:24:13.076 --> 00:24:14.369  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Full consortium.

438
00:24:17.956 --> 00:24:20.250  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Total monopoly.

439
00:24:20.625 --> 00:24:22.085  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-What?
-( Ferengis snickering )

440
00:24:25.422 --> 00:24:27.215  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You seem to be out of money.

441
00:24:27.841 --> 00:24:29.050  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Miles?

442
00:24:29.843 --> 00:24:30.886  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We're busted.

443
00:24:30.969 --> 00:24:32.220  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Thanks for the game.

444
00:24:32.304 --> 00:24:33.638  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Welcome back anytime.

445
00:24:33.722 --> 00:24:34.639  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
BASHIR: Wait.

446
00:24:34.723 --> 00:24:38.977  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Quark, did you really mean all that
about Dax...

447
00:24:39.311 --> 00:24:41.646  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Being my one last chance
for true happiness?

448
00:24:42.731 --> 00:24:48.653  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Doctor, you don't expect me
to show you all my cards, do you?

449
00:24:49.696 --> 00:24:51.072  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( money rattling )

450
00:24:52.490 --> 00:24:54.576  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sighs ) You lost.

451
00:24:54.659 --> 00:24:55.827  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What ever happened to "we"?

452
00:24:55.911 --> 00:25:00.790  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We weren't mooning over lost love
with a Ferengi holding a total monopoly.

453
00:25:01.416 --> 00:25:03.376  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You mean all that about Dax
was meant to distract me?

454
00:25:03.460 --> 00:25:05.003  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Obviously.

455
00:25:05.086 --> 00:25:07.130  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I can't believe I let him get to me.

456
00:25:07.214 --> 00:25:09.841  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Ah. Well... Not your fault.

457
00:25:11.259 --> 00:25:14.888  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Genetically engineered or not,
you're still "hu-man."

458
00:25:16.806 --> 00:25:18.808  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( rueful chuckling ) I guess.

459
00:25:19.559 --> 00:25:21.645  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Let's get a drink.
-( groaning )

460
00:25:46.294 --> 00:25:48.421  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( device humming )

461
00:26:07.065 --> 00:26:08.483  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Ow!

462
00:27:03.204 --> 00:27:04.581  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( shivering )

463
00:27:06.624 --> 00:27:09.377  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, let's not stand on pride, shall we?

464
00:27:09.669 --> 00:27:12.213  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Trills don't like the heat
and Klingons don't like the cold.

465
00:27:12.297 --> 00:27:14.174  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
There's no shame in admitting it.

466
00:27:15.133 --> 00:27:16.176  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Thank you.

467
00:27:16.259 --> 00:27:17.635  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You're welcome.

468
00:27:18.762 --> 00:27:20.764  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So, how are you enjoying your honeymoon?

469
00:27:20.847 --> 00:27:22.974  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Are you suffering enough?

470
00:27:23.058 --> 00:27:24.517  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Almost.

471
00:27:24.976 --> 00:27:26.895  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Is there anything I can get for you?

472
00:27:28.521 --> 00:27:29.689  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
More pain.

473
00:27:30.231 --> 00:27:31.358  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Less cold.

474
00:27:31.441 --> 00:27:32.942  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( laughing )

475
00:27:33.026 --> 00:27:35.195  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I don't know why that's funny, but it is.

476
00:27:35.278 --> 00:27:36.946  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( animal howling )

477
00:27:37.489 --> 00:27:38.990  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Mating call?

478
00:27:39.366 --> 00:27:40.950  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
500 meters.

479
00:27:41.701 --> 00:27:43.119  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That way.

480
00:27:43.203 --> 00:27:44.871  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( howling )

481
00:27:46.790 --> 00:27:48.500  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, that didn't take long.

482
00:27:49.209 --> 00:27:51.169  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Less than 300 meters.

483
00:27:51.252 --> 00:27:53.421  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( howling )

484
00:27:54.172 --> 00:27:56.674  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sighs ) Another happy couple.

485
00:28:01.930 --> 00:28:03.598  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
When I was a boy,

486
00:28:04.099 --> 00:28:08.269  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
my father used to take my brother and me
on camping trips in the Ural mountains.

487
00:28:10.105 --> 00:28:13.900  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Every night, we would listen to the wolves
howling in the distance.

488
00:28:15.360 --> 00:28:17.112  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Nikolai was afraid of them,

489
00:28:17.195 --> 00:28:20.615  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but I would lay in my tent for hours,
just listening.

490
00:28:23.201 --> 00:28:27.330  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I remember being seized by the urge
to just rip off my clothes

491
00:28:27.414 --> 00:28:29.833  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and run into the night
and live in the forest,

492
00:28:29.916 --> 00:28:33.044  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and become something... wild.

493
00:28:34.629 --> 00:28:36.423  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( howling )

494
00:28:39.676 --> 00:28:42.303  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
He must have been rejected.
He's moving away.

495
00:28:43.888 --> 00:28:45.265  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( howling and growling )

496
00:28:45.348 --> 00:28:46.975  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
She's not happy.

497
00:28:47.058 --> 00:28:48.143  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( twig snaps )

498
00:28:48.226 --> 00:28:49.853  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( growling )

499
00:28:49.936 --> 00:28:52.105  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
What? They're getting further away,
aren't they?

500
00:28:52.188 --> 00:28:55.608  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Yes, but it's because
something is coming.

501
00:28:57.485 --> 00:28:58.570  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And it is close.

502
00:29:13.126 --> 00:29:14.878  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( brush rustling )

503
00:29:27.098 --> 00:29:28.808  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( device beeping )

504
00:29:48.077 --> 00:29:49.579  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( yelling and grunting )

505
00:29:53.208 --> 00:29:55.668  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( strangled gurgling yell )

506
00:29:57.086 --> 00:29:58.379  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( groaning )

507
00:29:58.463 --> 00:30:00.089  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Jadzia!

508
00:30:00.799 --> 00:30:02.300  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( gasping )

509
00:30:06.221 --> 00:30:08.139  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( gasping )

510
00:30:10.141 --> 00:30:11.392  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Lie still.

511
00:30:11.476 --> 00:30:13.228  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I think I can do that.

512
00:30:14.521 --> 00:30:15.647  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( groaning )

513
00:30:15.730 --> 00:30:17.273  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Can I have the good news first?

514
00:30:20.735 --> 00:30:22.695  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No vital organs were damaged.

515
00:30:22.779 --> 00:30:24.864  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Now the bad news?

516
00:30:24.948 --> 00:30:27.659  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The disruptor burst
left an anti-coagulant in your system.

517
00:30:28.243 --> 00:30:30.703  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So you can't stop the bleeding?

518
00:30:30.787 --> 00:30:31.996  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No.

519
00:30:32.080 --> 00:30:34.958  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, I must not have taken
the whole burst.

520
00:30:35.416 --> 00:30:37.794  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm not hemorrhaging that bad yet.

521
00:30:37.877 --> 00:30:41.339  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Just keep me pumped full of painkillers,
and let's be on our way.

522
00:30:41.422 --> 00:30:42.882  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Moving could make the bleeding worse.

523
00:30:42.966 --> 00:30:44.968  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Staying here isn't an option.

524
00:30:45.510 --> 00:30:48.137  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Someone's going to come looking for them
when they don't check in,

525
00:30:48.221 --> 00:30:50.515  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and I'd rather take my chances on foot.

526
00:30:50.598 --> 00:30:51.683  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You ready?

527
00:30:53.893 --> 00:30:56.354  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-You ready?
-Ready.

528
00:30:56.729 --> 00:30:58.314  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Let's go.

529
00:30:58.857 --> 00:31:00.358  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( grunting )

530
00:31:15.373 --> 00:31:16.541  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( groans softly )

531
00:31:25.133 --> 00:31:27.844  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We are still 12 kilometers
from the rendezvous point.

532
00:31:27.927 --> 00:31:29.721  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And only 20 hours left.

533
00:31:30.221 --> 00:31:33.516  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, I guess it's time
we stop having so much fun

534
00:31:33.600 --> 00:31:35.351  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and pick up the pace, huh?

535
00:31:36.185 --> 00:31:38.062  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, more plasma.

536
00:31:38.146 --> 00:31:40.189  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No, thanks. I'm full. ( chuckles weakly )

537
00:31:41.190 --> 00:31:43.568  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Your blood pressure
has dropped another 20%.

538
00:31:43.651 --> 00:31:45.612  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Love that bedside manner.

539
00:31:45.695 --> 00:31:47.488  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You know, you should have been a doctor?

540
00:31:51.576 --> 00:31:53.995  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Your bandage will need to be changed soon.

541
00:31:54.537 --> 00:31:59.292  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, I think I'd like a blue
chiffon bandage this time,

542
00:31:59.375 --> 00:32:01.044  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
maybe some rhinestones.

543
00:32:01.127 --> 00:32:02.712  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Something with a little pizazz.

544
00:32:02.795 --> 00:32:04.380  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
This is no joking matter.

545
00:32:04.464 --> 00:32:05.673  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You are seriously injured,

546
00:32:05.757 --> 00:32:07.258  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and we have
a great deal of terrain to cover.

547
00:32:07.634 --> 00:32:09.928  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Just trying to lighten the mood.

548
00:32:10.011 --> 00:32:12.221  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
This is neither the time nor the place.

549
00:32:12.305 --> 00:32:14.474  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What happened to that new Worf?

550
00:32:14.557 --> 00:32:16.851  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You know, the one with the sense of humor?

551
00:32:17.727 --> 00:32:19.479  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That was a mistake.

552
00:32:19.562 --> 00:32:21.606  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, what is that supposed to mean?

553
00:32:21.689 --> 00:32:23.608  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It means if I had
not been joking with you,

554
00:32:23.691 --> 00:32:26.486  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I would not have allowed
the Jem'Hadar to get so close.

555
00:32:26.569 --> 00:32:29.113  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sighs ) So this is all my fault.

556
00:32:29.197 --> 00:32:30.657  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No.

557
00:32:30.740 --> 00:32:32.200  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It is mine.

558
00:32:32.867 --> 00:32:35.411  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I was trying to be something I am not.

559
00:32:35.495 --> 00:32:38.039  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
By letting down my guard,
by ignoring my duty,

560
00:32:38.122 --> 00:32:40.041  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I allowed my wife to be injured,

561
00:32:40.124 --> 00:32:42.502  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and I put the entire mission in jeopardy.

562
00:32:43.378 --> 00:32:44.879  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It will not happen again.

563
00:32:45.421 --> 00:32:46.923  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's not what happened.

564
00:32:48.007 --> 00:32:51.594  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Without our tricorders, there's no way--
-I do not wish to debate this.

565
00:32:53.680 --> 00:32:56.307  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We have a long way to go
and very little time.

566
00:32:57.183 --> 00:32:58.518  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Fine. Let's go.

567
00:32:59.227 --> 00:33:00.311  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( grunts )

568
00:33:27.505 --> 00:33:28.840  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( device beeping )

569
00:33:35.805 --> 00:33:36.931  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Ready?

570
00:33:37.724 --> 00:33:39.225  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( softly ) Yeah.

571
00:34:02.582 --> 00:34:03.958  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( groaning )

572
00:34:16.888 --> 00:34:18.806  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( groans )

573
00:34:24.520 --> 00:34:25.772  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hypo.

574
00:34:33.112 --> 00:34:34.530  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( groaning )

575
00:34:35.907 --> 00:34:38.326  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
There. Good as new.

576
00:34:44.832 --> 00:34:46.918  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I have to change your dressing.

577
00:34:47.001 --> 00:34:50.296  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's four bandages in two hours.

578
00:34:50.755 --> 00:34:52.799  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's got to be some kind of record.

579
00:34:53.299 --> 00:34:57.470  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Oh, sorry. I forgot the new rules.
Nothing funny.

580
00:34:57.553 --> 00:34:59.055  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Got to be serious.

581
00:34:59.138 --> 00:35:00.932  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Life and death.

582
00:35:01.015 --> 00:35:02.642  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We've got a job to do.

583
00:35:06.187 --> 00:35:08.648  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Jadzia, I know you are tired,

584
00:35:08.731 --> 00:35:12.610  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but we have to cover three kilometers
before nightfall. Can you do it?

585
00:35:13.611 --> 00:35:15.822  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
As long as you got those painkillers,

586
00:35:15.905 --> 00:35:18.407  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'll follow you
through the gates of hell, sir.

587
00:35:19.909 --> 00:35:20.743  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hmm...

588
00:35:20.827 --> 00:35:23.871  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, that was almost a smile.

589
00:35:27.542 --> 00:35:31.462  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
When this mission is over,
I will smile all you want.

590
00:35:31.963 --> 00:35:33.422  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, you promise?

591
00:35:34.090 --> 00:35:35.424  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I promise.

592
00:35:37.135 --> 00:35:40.346  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Then let's finish this mission
and get out of here.

593
00:35:42.431 --> 00:35:43.975  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( both grunt )

594
00:35:44.058 --> 00:35:45.643  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Whoa.

595
00:35:45.726 --> 00:35:46.769  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( groans )

596
00:35:46.853 --> 00:35:48.396  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's all right, I can stand.

597
00:35:48.479 --> 00:35:49.814  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Just help me get my balance.

598
00:35:49.897 --> 00:35:51.315  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Help me balance.

599
00:35:52.150 --> 00:35:53.818  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Or maybe not.

600
00:35:54.152 --> 00:35:55.570  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( gasps )

601
00:35:58.906 --> 00:36:00.408  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( grunting )

602
00:36:05.371 --> 00:36:06.581  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( beeping )

603
00:36:09.041 --> 00:36:12.295  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Let me guess. Things aren't looking up.

604
00:36:12.795 --> 00:36:14.881  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
There's been another drop
in your blood pressure.

605
00:36:14.964 --> 00:36:17.049  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And your neural E.D.L. readings
are erratic.

606
00:36:18.009 --> 00:36:20.553  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So what's your prescription, doc?

607
00:36:21.679 --> 00:36:24.140  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Surgery... at a Starbase.

608
00:36:24.223 --> 00:36:26.767  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Could I get a second opinion?

609
00:36:33.858 --> 00:36:37.528  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Worf, you have to go on without me...

610
00:36:38.112 --> 00:36:39.488  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And I know that.

611
00:36:39.572 --> 00:36:41.199  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I understand.

612
00:36:41.282 --> 00:36:43.826  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
My duty requires
that I complete the mission

613
00:36:43.910 --> 00:36:45.620  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
regardless of my personal feelings.

614
00:36:46.245 --> 00:36:47.330  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Absolutely.

615
00:36:47.413 --> 00:36:49.207  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You're a Starfleet officer.

616
00:36:49.290 --> 00:36:51.792  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So am I, and I understand.

617
00:36:52.251 --> 00:36:56.380  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The information Lasaran has could be
potentially invaluable to the war effort.

618
00:36:56.464 --> 00:36:59.175  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You don't have to explain to me.

619
00:36:59.675 --> 00:37:01.510  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm hurt. You're not.

620
00:37:02.345 --> 00:37:04.680  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And there's a job to be done.

621
00:37:04.764 --> 00:37:06.265  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I will be back tomorrow night.

622
00:37:08.226 --> 00:37:09.769  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Don't worry.

623
00:37:09.852 --> 00:37:11.395  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm not going anywhere.

624
00:37:12.021 --> 00:37:15.650  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I can have you in the stasis chamber
on the runabout in 45 hours.

625
00:37:17.193 --> 00:37:18.527  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No problem.

626
00:37:19.487 --> 00:37:21.030  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I will leave the med kit.

627
00:37:21.113 --> 00:37:23.741  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Scan yourself with the tricorder
every half hour.

628
00:37:23.824 --> 00:37:25.576  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The plasma hypospray will be set--

629
00:37:26.160 --> 00:37:29.580  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I took basic first aid.
I know what I have to do.

630
00:37:34.210 --> 00:37:35.294  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Worf.

631
00:37:37.338 --> 00:37:39.966  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's been a great two months, hasn't it?

632
00:37:43.427 --> 00:37:44.470  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yes.

633
00:37:48.349 --> 00:37:51.727  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Jadzia, I just want to tell you how--

634
00:37:52.812 --> 00:37:54.563  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( whispers ) Just kiss me and go.

635
00:38:17.628 --> 00:38:18.629  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sobbing )

636
00:38:34.729 --> 00:38:37.106  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( heart beating )

637
00:38:49.327 --> 00:38:52.330  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( beating louder )

638
00:39:18.939 --> 00:39:19.982  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sighs )

639
00:39:42.129 --> 00:39:43.339  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What's the word?

640
00:39:47.259 --> 00:39:49.095  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
She is still in surgery,

641
00:39:49.178 --> 00:39:52.473  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but Dr. Bashir is hopeful
she will make a full recovery.

642
00:39:53.599 --> 00:39:54.767  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Lasaran's dead.

643
00:39:54.850 --> 00:39:57.186  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Starfleet intelligence
intercepted a transmission

644
00:39:57.269 --> 00:40:00.940  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
saying that he'd been killed
trying to reenter the base at Soukara.

645
00:40:01.023 --> 00:40:02.983  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Could you have made the rendezvous?

646
00:40:03.067 --> 00:40:04.235  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yes.

647
00:40:04.944 --> 00:40:07.571  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-But yet you turned back to save Jadzia.
-Yes.

648
00:40:07.863 --> 00:40:09.907  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Were you aware that
the information that man had

649
00:40:09.990 --> 00:40:12.076  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
could have saved millions of lives?

650
00:40:13.035 --> 00:40:14.120  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yes.

651
00:40:14.578 --> 00:40:15.871  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So what happened?

652
00:40:17.415 --> 00:40:20.000  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-You may not understand.
-Try me, sir.

653
00:40:23.045 --> 00:40:24.672  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You were at my wedding.

654
00:40:24.755 --> 00:40:27.091  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You heard the story
of the first two Klingon hearts

655
00:40:27.174 --> 00:40:28.926  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and how nothing could stand against them

656
00:40:29.009 --> 00:40:32.138  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and how they even destroyed
the Gods that had created them.

657
00:40:32.763 --> 00:40:35.433  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I have heard that story since I was a boy,

658
00:40:36.016 --> 00:40:37.935  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
but I never understood it...

659
00:40:38.018 --> 00:40:40.020  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I mean really understood it...

660
00:40:40.771 --> 00:40:44.525  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Until I was standing in the jungle
with my heart pounding in my chest,

661
00:40:44.608 --> 00:40:48.112  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and I found that even I could
not stand against my own heart.

662
00:40:48.654 --> 00:40:50.322  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I had to go back.

663
00:40:51.365 --> 00:40:53.033  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And it did not matter
what Starfleet thought,

664
00:40:53.117 --> 00:40:54.452  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
or what the consequences were.

665
00:40:54.535 --> 00:40:57.455  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
She was my wife and I could not leave her.

666
00:40:58.706 --> 00:41:01.750  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
As your captain,
it is my duty to inform you

667
00:41:01.834 --> 00:41:03.961  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
that you made the wrong choice.

668
00:41:05.337 --> 00:41:08.215  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I don't think Starfleet will file
any formal charges.

669
00:41:09.175 --> 00:41:11.218  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Even a secret court-martial
would run the risk

670
00:41:11.302 --> 00:41:14.305  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
of revealing too much about
their intelligence operations.

671
00:41:15.723 --> 00:41:18.350  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But this will go into your service record.

672
00:41:20.060 --> 00:41:22.938  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And to be completely honest,

673
00:41:23.022 --> 00:41:26.650  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
you probably won't be offered
a command on your own after this.

674
00:41:28.652 --> 00:41:29.904  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I understand.

675
00:41:29.987 --> 00:41:32.323  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I've also issued new orders.

676
00:41:32.406 --> 00:41:34.617  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You and Jadzia are not
to be assigned to a mission

677
00:41:34.700 --> 00:41:36.785  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
on your own ever again.

678
00:41:42.082 --> 00:41:43.876  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And one last thing.

679
00:41:45.127 --> 00:41:47.296  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
As a man who had a wife...

680
00:41:49.381 --> 00:41:52.176  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If Jennifer had been
lying in that clearing...

681
00:41:53.469 --> 00:41:55.679  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I wouldn't have left her either.

682
00:42:01.936 --> 00:42:03.270  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( door opens )

683
00:42:22.998 --> 00:42:24.250  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hey.

684
00:42:25.292 --> 00:42:26.669  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( whispers ) I know you.

685
00:42:28.045 --> 00:42:29.255  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We have met.

686
00:42:30.005 --> 00:42:32.049  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Ah, you're joking again.

687
00:42:32.716 --> 00:42:34.260  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's a good sign.

688
00:42:35.386 --> 00:42:37.263  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Did you make the rendezvous?

689
00:42:38.722 --> 00:42:39.640  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No.

690
00:42:41.684 --> 00:42:43.602  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( softly) I could not leave you there.

691
00:42:44.687 --> 00:42:48.732  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Not for Lasaran, not for the mission,
not for anything else.

692
00:42:49.733 --> 00:42:51.151  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Lasaran?

693
00:42:53.112 --> 00:42:54.280  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Dead.

694
00:42:55.239 --> 00:42:56.907  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Are you in trouble?

695
00:42:56.991 --> 00:42:58.742  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I have been in trouble before.

696
00:42:59.952 --> 00:43:01.537  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm sorry.

697
00:43:02.246 --> 00:43:03.914  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I should have kept going.

698
00:43:04.582 --> 00:43:07.001  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You have nothing to be sorry about.

699
00:43:08.502 --> 00:43:11.088  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I know how much your career means to you.

700
00:43:12.006 --> 00:43:13.549  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You come first.

701
00:43:14.300 --> 00:43:17.928  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Before career, before duty,
before anything.

702
00:43:19.179 --> 00:43:21.473  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I do not regret what I did,

703
00:43:23.183 --> 00:43:25.144  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and I would do it again.

704
00:43:26.812 --> 00:43:28.814  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I don't know what to say.

705
00:43:30.441 --> 00:43:34.069  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You could say,
"Thank you for saving my life."

706
00:43:36.405 --> 00:43:38.532  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Thank you for saving my life.

707
00:43:39.491 --> 00:43:42.620  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And you could say,
"I would do the same for you, Worf."

708
00:43:43.495 --> 00:43:47.041  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well... I'd have to think about that.

709
00:43:48.000 --> 00:43:50.878  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
My career is very important to me,
you know.

710
00:43:51.920 --> 00:43:54.131  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sighs )

711
00:43:56.258 --> 00:43:58.218  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And you could say, "I love you."

712
00:44:02.097 --> 00:44:03.974  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I love you.

713
00:44:05.267 --> 00:44:06.644  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And I love you.

